1
00:00:09,967 --> 00:00:12,233
Look, we're
manipulating this post.

2
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,433
Even the metadata was tweaked

3
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,100
to make it trace back
to the pastor's church.

4
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,633
We can find out who posted that.

5
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:21,367
Bet you won't like this.

6
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:22,733
Pastor Ferdie?!

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,433
What a complete bastard!

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,233
You've got some nerve!

9
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,033
Weren't you fighting
with Matthias?

10
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:31,133
That post was traced back
to this location!

11
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:34,400
That's exactly what
he wants you to believe!

12
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,400
Moron!

13
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,433
Your secrets are spilling out

14
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:39,933
because you don't know
how to cover your tracks!

15
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:43,100
Watch me expose
all your dirt, Pastor.

16
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,100
I'll make you regret this.

17
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:50,933
[BLOWS LANDING]

18
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:54,100
Settle down,
or we'll kill you all!

19
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,567
Oh, please!
Watch where you're going!

20
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:03,800
Sorry...

21
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,833
Diane, don't go through
with your plan.

22
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:08,000
Just let me do this, please.

23
00:01:08,167 --> 00:01:10,267
If your contact won't help us,

24
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:12,367
then this might be
my only chance.

25
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,667
You really think you can
escape from here?

26
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:18,200
There are guards everywhere.

27
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,967
Looks like one phone's missing.

28
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,433
Someone escaped!

29
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:28,100
[ALARM BLARING]

30
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,133
- Gavin, run! Call for help!
- Hurry!

31
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:31,167
- Gavin!
- Pa!

32
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:32,633
We're trying to escape!

33
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:33,767
Where are you?

34
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:35,967
Gavin!

35
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:37,200
[GUNSHOT]

36
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:38,867
My son!

37
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,500
Talk to me!

38
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,367
Please say something!

39
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:44,200
He and Matthias have issues
with each other.

40
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:45,833
Then they dragged me into it.

41
00:01:45,933 --> 00:01:47,333
Crazy, right?

42
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:49,467
Do you really think Matthias was
 the one who framed you?

43
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:50,900
Who else?

44
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:53,000
He's the only one skilled enough
 with that kind of technology.

45
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:54,300
Everything's such a mess!

46
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:58,167
General, how's your health?

47
00:01:58,267 --> 00:01:59,867
A billion dollars.

48
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:01,967
You have to talk to them.

49
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:04,833
They're desperate enough
to replace you.

50
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,900
Hmm.

51
00:02:06,667 --> 00:02:08,200
I don't like internal conflict.

52
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:10,000
That's precisely why I'm here.

53
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:13,667
To express my disapproval
of my brother's recent actions.

54
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,367
What do you think, Samuel?

55
00:02:15,533 --> 00:02:17,267
General, what's the plan here?

56
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:20,700
Is Samuel going to replace you?

57
00:02:20,867 --> 00:02:22,367
Only when I'm gone.

58
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:25,700
But as long as I'm alive,
it's status quo.

59
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:28,500
I'm still the head of Bakunawa.

60
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:36,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,933
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

62
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,967
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,600
General, we'll go ahead.

64
00:02:59,767 --> 00:03:00,633
Alright.

65
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:13,233
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

66
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:15,700
[FIRE CRACKLING]

67
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,900
[VALENTINO SCREAMS]

68
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,767
- The Old--
- Oh my god!

69
00:03:18,933 --> 00:03:19,767
[SAMEUL COUGHS]

70
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,800
- Oh my god! General!
- The Old Man!

71
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:24,833
[SAMUEL COUGHING]

72
00:03:24,967 --> 00:03:26,767
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:03:26,867 --> 00:03:28,000
[GROANS]

74
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,400
Argh...

75
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,800
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

76
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,233
Agh!

77
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,233
[GROANS, EXHALES HEAVILY]

78
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,800
[GROANING]

79
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:45,900
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

81
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,933
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

82
00:03:49,033 --> 00:03:50,233
[CRACKLING CONTINUES]

83
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,267
The Old Man is dead.

84
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:57,133
[GROANING, GRUNTING]

85
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:59,633
General!

86
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:00,800
[VALENTINO SOBBING]

87
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:01,967
[FIRE ROARING]

88
00:04:02,067 --> 00:04:03,267
[PANICKED BREATHS]

89
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:09,933
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,167
[GRUNTS]

91
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,367
[BOTH GROANING, GRUNTING]

92
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:26,333
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

93
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,133
[SAMUEL] Slowly now!

94
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:30,200
- [SAMUEL GRUNTS]
- [DIEGO GROANING WEAKLY]

95
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:38,000
[BOTH GRUNTING, GROANING]

96
00:04:38,167 --> 00:04:45,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:48,833
This way!

98
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,200
Take it easy.
Let's stop right here and sit.

99
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:58,867
[DIEGO BREATHING SHARPLY]

100
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:06,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:10,367
[SAMUEL BREATHING HEAVILY]

102
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:12,767
[DIEGO PANTING]

103
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,167
[CRYING]

104
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:21,100
You think Gavin
and the others are okay?

105
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:22,533
I hope so.

106
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:25,367
I-I really hope they're okay.

107
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:28,833
[BOTH CRYING]

109
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:30,567
Thank you, Naomi.

110
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,767
For knocking some sense
into me.

111
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:35,900
I was so stubborn.

112
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:37,633
Sorry.

113
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,867
I just want
to see my mother again.

114
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:43,233
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,800
It's okay. It's okay.

116
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:48,900
I know how you feel.
Because I feel it too.

117
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,567
My mother is sick.

118
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,267
I want to be with her again
so badly.

119
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:56,300
I miss her so much.

120
00:05:56,433 --> 00:06:03,300
[DIANE, NAOMI SOBBING]

121
00:06:03,433 --> 00:06:04,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

122
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:08,633
You think we'll ever
make it out alive?

123
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:11,933
I don't know.

124
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,100
I have no idea.
I really don't.

125
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:22,467
[DIANE SOBBING, SNIFFLING]

126
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:24,500
[NAOMI CRIES] I'm sorry.

127
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:31,067
- [MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BOTH SOBBING]

128
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:33,267
[DOCTOR] Give me the rundown.

129
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:34,333
[NURSE 1] Male 1. Mid-30s.

130
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:35,767
With burns from a car explosion.

131
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:38,267
- What's his BP?
- 85 over 59, doc.

132
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:39,467
Tachycardia.

133
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:41,100
[NURSE 2] Male, doc.

134
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:42,633
Mid-60s to early 70s.

135
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:44,667
With burns from a car explosion.

136
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:45,767
Unconscious.

137
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:47,800
BP, 82 over 57.

138
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:50,267
[HEARTBEAT POUNDING]

139
00:06:50,367 --> 00:06:57,433
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,000
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:08,633
[REPORTER ON TV]
 Breaking news!

142
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:11,133
A suspected assassination
attempt is being investigated

143
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:13,967
following the car explosion
involving the Scam Buster,

144
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,833
retired police general

145
00:07:15,933 --> 00:07:17,033
Diego Ramirez.

146
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,667
According to official reports,

147
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,300
Samuel Trinidad was seen
in the area

148
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,633
at the time of the incident.

149
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:24,000
It's worth noting that
only a few months ago,

150
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:25,500
Samuel Trinidad was involved

151
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,667
in the Yayaman Tayo
Investment Scam

152
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:29,633
linked to his father,
Mike Trinidad.

153
00:07:29,733 --> 00:07:32,300
Several other prominent figures
were also spotted at the scene,

154
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,300
including Roldan Rivera,

155
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,300
CEO of Oriental Ridge Estates,

156
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,633
food vlogger Sunshine Meloria,

157
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:41,133
basketball player
Peter Montecillo,

158
00:07:41,233 --> 00:07:45,733
recently controversial fashion
designer Valentino Narciso,

159
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:48,733
and church leader
Pastor Ferdinand Almonte.

160
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,867
General Joel Balagtas is
joining us now

161
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:52,900
to give a statement

162
00:07:53,067 --> 00:07:54,200
regarding the incident.

163
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,367
[JOEL] The entire police force
 strongly condemns

164
00:07:57,533 --> 00:08:00,033
the violence that has befallen
General Ramirez.

165
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,533
There is no doubt it was
an assassination attempt,

166
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,900
given the number of criminals
he helped put behind bars.

167
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:08,567
Rest assured that
we will not stop

168
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:10,400
until we apprehend the culprit.

169
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,033
[REMOTE CLATTERS]

170
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:14,267
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,533
[PHONE RINGS]

172
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:18,033
Did you do it?

173
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,100
What are you talking about?

174
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,133
Why would I do that?
Maybe it was you!

175
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:24,867
Definitely not me!

176
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,433
Then that leaves Jacob
as the prime suspect.

177
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:31,100
We're absolutely going
to get dragged into this.

178
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,433
We speak out
against the Old Man.

179
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,433
Chances are, we'll be
on his list of suspects.

180
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,767
That's why I'm already
preparing on my end.

182
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:43,133
S-Someone might come barging
in any moment.

183
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:46,533
That damn Jacob is
nothing but trouble.

184
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:49,800
So if I were you,
I'd start getting ready too.

185
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:59,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,167
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,600
- Sir.
- What?

188
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:09,800
What's going on, officer?

189
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:11,500
Sir, have you heard the news?

190
00:09:12,167 --> 00:09:13,300
- What news?
- Sir.

191
00:09:13,467 --> 00:09:15,900
Someone blew up
General Ramirez's car.

192
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,100
What?

193
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,933
And he was with Samuel Trinidad.

194
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,233
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

195
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,300
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

196
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,667
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

197
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,700
Enzo, are you sure you're okay?

198
00:09:36,667 --> 00:09:39,000
It's a lot to take in, Arissa.

199
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:44,633
So that's it?

200
00:09:44,733 --> 00:09:48,033
He'll leave the syndicate
and turn over a new leaf.

201
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:50,933
What about all the people
who were affected?

202
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:52,967
Pretend like nothing happened?
Is that really it?

203
00:09:54,133 --> 00:09:55,000
Enzo.

204
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:57,033
The truth is,

205
00:09:57,667 --> 00:09:59,300
I hate your father.

206
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:01,667
I can't forgive him
for everything

207
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:03,633
he put my family through.

208
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,167
And for what happened
to Rainier.

209
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:08,667
But if he's trying to change
for the better,

210
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:10,300
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,967
maybe it's a start.

212
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:14,833
He's doing it to earn
your forgiveness.

213
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:18,967
I can hold a grudge against him
my whole life.

214
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,333
I don't have to love him.

215
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:24,700
But you?

216
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:26,733
He's your father.

217
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,233
[GATE HANDLE CLANKING]

218
00:10:29,433 --> 00:10:31,233
[ARISSA] Auntie, what happened?

219
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,367
[LOLITA] Uh...

220
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,467
It's your brother.

221
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:34,800
He was rushed to the hospital.

222
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:37,567
They say he got hurt
in that car explosion.

223
00:10:37,733 --> 00:10:38,700
- What?!
- It's true.

224
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:39,833
Let's check on him.

225
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:41,433
Miss Lolita,
let me drive you there.

226
00:10:41,567 --> 00:10:42,900
- Come.
- I'll look after King.

227
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:44,733
- Go, Miss Lolita.
- Thank you, Boying.

228
00:10:45,467 --> 00:10:46,433
Arissa, get in the car.

229
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:50,200
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

230
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,200
[ENZO GRUNTS]

231
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,700
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

232
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,900
[ENGINE STARTS]

233
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:57,700
[ENGINE REVVING]

234
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:05,333
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,400
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

236
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:11,767
Going to see the general?

237
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,567
He's in Room 308.

238
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:16,467
[LEAH] I know.
Were you there just now?

239
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:19,267
How is he?

240
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:21,667
I haven't dropped by yet.

241
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:24,067
Still, he's probably fine.
At least that's what they say.

242
00:11:24,067 --> 00:11:25,600
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,467
What exactly happened?

244
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:29,133
Someone planted a bomb
in his car.

245
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,967
What?!

246
00:11:30,967 --> 00:11:34,000
Nothing's confirmed yet,
so let's keep it under wraps.

247
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,933
It looks like
an assassination attempt.

248
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:36,767
What?!

249
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:40,000
Who would do that?

250
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,067
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

251
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,833
We are still investigating.

252
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:46,167
But with the number of criminals
who hate him,

253
00:11:46,167 --> 00:11:48,833
the list of suspects is
quite long.

254
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,333
By the way,
someone saved his life.

255
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:52,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:53,567
That scammer.

257
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:55,833
Samuel Trinidad.

258
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:58,600
It's funny.

259
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:02,300
The Scam Buster owes his life
to a scammer.

260
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:05,767
Any idea what
ties them together?

261
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:09,633
Yes.

262
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:12,267
Because I am the mother
of Samuel's son.

263
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:14,367
King is my son.

264
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,700
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

265
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,000
Wow.

266
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,500
You're no different
from the general.

267
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,667
Both have children born
out of wedlock.

268
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,867
What a chaotic family
we've got, huh?

269
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:24,700
[JOHNNY CHUCKLES]

270
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:27,700
Well, welcome to the family.

271
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:29,533
Brother.

272
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:35,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:36,533
Brother?

274
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:40,800
[SNICKERS]
Brother.

275
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:44,233
[GRAVEL CRUNCHING]

276
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:45,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

277
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,333
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

278
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:50,333
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

279
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,900
[FERDIE]
Your brother is out of control!

280
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:54,900
What if we had died?
What if the Old Man had died?

281
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:57,433
[ROLDAN] Wait a minute,
why are you blaming my brother?

282
00:12:57,433 --> 00:12:58,733
What does he have
to do with that?

283
00:12:58,733 --> 00:13:00,533
[VALENTINO] Oh, please!
It's so obvious!

284
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:04,567
Your brother almost cost me
my flawless face!

285
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:09,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,267
[LINE RINGING]

287
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,533
Jacob, pick up.

288
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,567
Tell him to thread lightly.

289
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:18,400
If you doesn't,
I'll come for him myself!

290
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,200
I dare you to lay a hand
on my brother.

291
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,367
We'll have a problem.

292
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:25,533
Now hold on. Where were
Abel and Matthias again?

293
00:13:25,533 --> 00:13:27,300
They weren't at the meeting,
were they?!

294
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,800
All of us want the
Old Man's role, don't we?

296
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,933
Then every single one
of us can be a target.

297
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:35,333
I won't have any of it!

298
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,533
Remember our agreement.

299
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:42,700
The Bakunawa can go
for each other's throats,

300
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,467
but we leave out families
out of it!

301
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:45,700
That's where we find
common ground.

302
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,300
I agree with you
on that, Pastor.

303
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:49,567
I hope your brother honors that.

304
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:51,433
Or he'll face consequences!

305
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:55,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

306
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:58,233
[VALENTINO] Oh my god,
what a dirty place!

307
00:13:58,233 --> 00:13:59,033
[CAR DOORS OPENING]

308
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,433
[ENGINES STARTING]

309
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:02,633
[FERDIE] Let's go!

310
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:03,733
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

311
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:08,467
- [GRAVEL CRUNCHING]
- [LINE RINGING]

312
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:10,600
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,333
[PHONE RINGING]

314
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:13,767
Jacob, pick up your phone!

315
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:17,133
Who is that?

316
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:18,400
Come on, answer it.

317
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,133
- It's Roldan. Hello--
 - Jacob!

318
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:23,400
What did you do this time?!

319
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,433
What do you mean?

320
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:27,933
The Old Man's car exploded!

321
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,867
I almost died!
What's wrong with you?

322
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:32,700
Hang on. What were you
doing with him?

323
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:34,967
Jacob, I was trying
to protect you!

324
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,833
What the hell was that?
Explain yourself!

325
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:38,167
You nearly got me killed!

326
00:14:38,167 --> 00:14:39,800
Wait, wait.
I had nothing to do with it.

327
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:41,000
I didn't do anything.

328
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Come on now.

329
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,000
When are you going
to believe me?

330
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,500
Jacob, listen to me.

331
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,967
I don't know if he's
regained consciousness.

332
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:52,033
But if I were you,
I'd go into hiding.

333
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:53,800
Because if he has,

334
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:56,900
you're the only one
he'll blame!

335
00:14:58,167 --> 00:14:59,167
Remember that!

336
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:02,033
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

337
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:08,933
[MUSIC SWELLING]

338
00:15:19,867 --> 00:15:20,667
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
- [LOLITA CRIES]

339
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:21,700
Son...

340
00:15:21,867 --> 00:15:22,933
[WEAKLY] Ma...

341
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:24,533
Ma...

342
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:26,933
[CRYING, SNIFFLES]

343
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,333
Does anything hurt?

344
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,333
How are you feeling, son?

345
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,400
I'm okay.

346
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:38,800
I'm okay, really.

347
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:41,733
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

348
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:42,967
[SNIFFLES]

349
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:44,967
[DOOR OPENS]

350
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:47,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:48,733
[LOLITA SNIFFLES]

352
00:15:51,933 --> 00:15:53,233
Dad hasn't woken up yet,

353
00:15:54,267 --> 00:15:56,967
but the doctors said
he's going to be okay.

354
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,733
Thanks for saving his life.

355
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:03,567
But I hope you know this
doesn't change anything.

356
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,333
I'm still taking my son back.

357
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:09,167
But I do hope you feel better.

358
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:13,000
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

359
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:14,333
Get well soon.

360
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:21,833
Enzo.

361
00:16:21,967 --> 00:16:23,167
Hi, Auntie.

362
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,100
I'm glad your dad is okay.

363
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:27,767
Thank you.

364
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

365
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:32,100
[DOOR OPENS]

366
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:35,733
[DOOR CLOSES]

367
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,200
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

368
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:50,700
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:51,700
[SLAMS CABINET]

370
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,033
[GRUNTS]

371
00:16:54,167 --> 00:16:56,133
[INHALES, EXHALES HEAVILY]

372
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:03,733
[PHONE RINGING]

373
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,567
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:17:06,667 --> 00:17:07,567
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

375
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,267
Enzo.

376
00:17:10,567 --> 00:17:11,533
Hello, Pa?

377
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:12,967
Pa, are you okay?

378
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:15,567
I heard you were there when
General Ramirez's car blew up.

379
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,667
Y-Yes.

380
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,967
I'm okay. Uh...

381
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:21,500
We had a meeting in the area,
but I wasn't hurt.

382
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:22,567
I'm okay.

383
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,133
[RELIEVED SIGH]

384
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:25,733
Good to know, Pa.

385
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:27,500
Uh...

386
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:29,067
Pa?

387
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,433
Want to...

388
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,833
grab lunch tomorrow?

389
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:34,067
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

390
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,733
I was hoping we could talk, too.

391
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:37,567
If that's okay with you.

392
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:39,300
Sure, sure.

393
00:17:39,867 --> 00:17:40,800
Sure, Enzo.

394
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,667
Uh, son?

395
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:44,733
It means a lot that you called.

396
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:47,467
Alright, Pa.
I'll see you tomorrow.

397
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:52,433
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

398
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:53,767
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

399
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:54,867
You did good.

400
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:10,700
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

401
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,700
He said he was trying to escape,

402
00:18:12,867 --> 00:18:15,367
and then the call got cut off.

403
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:18,367
I tried calling back,
over and over,

404
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:20,800
but...

405
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:22,633
no one's answering.

406
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:24,833
He's not picking up.

407
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:26,900
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

408
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:30,467
I don't know what happened
to my son.

409
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:34,233
I don't know...

410
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,733
if they're hurting Gavin.

411
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:38,533
Or if...

412
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:41,133
- Paulo, it's okay.
- What--

413
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:42,233
- Paulo.
- What if--

414
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:44,400
- Paulo, calm down.
- What if--

415
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,333
- Calm down. Take deep breaths.
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

416
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:48,833
- Just breathe.
- [SNIFFLING]

417
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:52,467
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

418
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,500
- [LEN SNIFFLES]
- [PAULO] M-Miss Bebina.

419
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,267
I don't know what I'll do

420
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:59,767
if something terrible has
happened to Gavin.

421
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,033
I won't survive the pain.

422
00:19:04,133 --> 00:19:05,267
[RAGGED BREATHS]

423
00:19:05,433 --> 00:19:07,167
- It'll destroy me, Miss Bebina!
- [LEN] Paulo...

424
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:08,600
Paulo, try to calm down.

425
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:09,667
[LEN] Paulo...

426
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,900
Paulo, don't lose hope.

427
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:14,200
Our children will be safe.

428
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:15,767
[LEN WHIMPERING]

429
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:17,000
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

430
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:20,067
[BEBINA]
Stay strong for your children.

431
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,433
For now,

432
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:25,733
all you can do is
hold on to hope

433
00:19:26,567 --> 00:19:31,200
and trust that
they'll be returned to you.

434
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:34,733
[LEN, PAULO CRYING]

435
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:36,067
Gavin...

436
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:37,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

437
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:38,400
Gavin!

438
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,533
My son!

439
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,033
[JACOB BREATHES SHARPLY]

441
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,633
Who could've attacked
the Old Man?

442
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,500
Who was it? Abel or Matthias?

443
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,400
[HUFFS]

444
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

445
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:12,967
[CHUCKLES DRYLY]

446
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,933
It was Trinidad.

447
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,333
I'm sure it was Trinidad!

448
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:28,167
Gavin, one of the prisoners,
is dead.

449
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,433
I won't survive the pain!

450
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:32,233
I'm trying to find an angle
on the recent explosion.

451
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:35,733
What were you doing
with General Diego Ramirez?

452
00:20:36,467 --> 00:20:39,800
Bring me Matthias and Abel.

453
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,167
What about Jacob Rivera, sir?

454
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,933
I want him dead.

455
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:46,767
Don't let anyone get near
or breach the perimeter.

456
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:47,933
We can handle this.

457
00:20:48,067 --> 00:20:49,667
Just like before,
as long as we stick together.

458
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,700
[GUNSHOTS]

459
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:54,133
Sins of the Father:
The Impending Finale
